<CAPTION>  Photo; DRAWING: Dr. Seuss' 'How the Grinch Stole Christmas' is part of a
triple bill on TNT.  </CAPTION>
<DESCRIPT>  TELEVISION; REVIEW; BRIEF  </DESCRIPT>
<LEADPARA>  Commercial Broadcast; 9:30 p.m. Next Step CH4 Richard Hart describes high-tech
advances in computer music interfaces, movie special effects and other
futuristic technology, and takes a look at high-tech holiday gifts.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  Living  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  HIGHLIGHTS  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>  Cable; 4:30 p.m. Dr. Seuss Triple Feature TNT. Three of the author's tales are
featured. First "The Butter Battle Book," followed by "How the Grinch Stole
Christmas" at 5 p.m. and "The 5,000 Fingers of Dr. T" at 5:30 p.m. (Continues
until 7:30 p.m.); 6 p.m. You Can't Cheat an Honest Man SHOW. W.C. Fields
trades barbs with Charlie McCarthy and Edgar Bergen and tries to keep his
circus from going bankrupt in this hilarious 1939 comedy.; 7:05 p.m. The Bells
of St. Mary's (Color) TBS. Bing Crosby reprises his Father O'Malley role from
"Going My Way" and tries to work miracles at a rundown church in this 1945
drama. Ingrid Bergman co-stars.; PBS; 11 p.m. Lionel at Lied CH60 Vibraphonist
Lionel Hampton and his band perform in Nebraska.; Talk Shows; 9 a.m. Sally
Jessy Raphael CH7 CH8 Unsung heroes.; 9 a.m. Geraldo CH11 Abduction of
children by parents. (Also 3 p.m. CH4); 3 p.m. Oprah Winfrey CH7 CH8 Couples
divided over having a baby.; 3:30 p.m. Up Close ESPN. Wayne Gretzky.; Radio; 8
p.m. KKHI-AM (1550) and KKHI-FM (95.7) Detroit Symphony Orchestra: Works by
Bortz, Cimarosa, Mozart and Beethoven.; 8:30 p.m. KALW-FM (91.7) Sherlock
Holmes: "The Adventure of the Speckled Band."; 10 p.m. KFRC-AM (610) The Larry
King Show: Film critic Leonard Maltin.  </TEXT>
